From 1ef77fe7fab9501740ceb590ea79b3ef7eca4395 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: andrew <andrew@anyscale.com>
Date: Wed, 25 Feb 2026 13:59:45 -0800
Subject: [PATCH 10/10] use compiler_param_file on Windows to avoid
 CreateProcessW limit

Backport of https://github.com/ray-project/ray/pull/61294.
On Windows, the raylet compilation command exceeds the 32,767 character
CreateProcessW limit due to accumulated /I include paths. The
compiler_param_file feature writes compiler args to a response file
instead. This is only enabled for the raylet target on Windows to avoid
breaking external dependencies like lzma that can't parse param files.

Signed-off-by: andrew <andrew@anyscale.com>
---
 src/ray/raylet/BUILD.bazel | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/ray/raylet/BUILD.bazel b/src/ray/raylet/BUILD.bazel
index e311945758..44bb1a05c5 100644
--- a/src/ray/raylet/BUILD.bazel
+++ b/src/ray/raylet/BUILD.bazel
@@ -272,6 +272,10 @@ ray_cc_library(
 ray_cc_binary(
     name = "raylet",
     srcs = ["main.cc"],
+    features = select({
+        "@platforms//os:windows": ["compiler_param_file"],
+        "//conditions:default": [],
+    }),
     visibility = ["//visibility:public"],
     deps = [
         ":local_object_manager",
-- 
